        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 7:00PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 700 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near North Georgia Speedway,
or near Chatsworth, moving southeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, nickel sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Dalton, Chatsworth, Varnell, Dawnville, Ramhurst, Rocky Face, Fort
Mountain State Park, and North Georgia Speedway.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
